main event: A witness observed a satellite-like object in the sky for 1 hour and 30 minutes on May 1, 1956.
interesting points: The object appeared like a star with a circle around it,The size of the object was approximately that of a grapefruit,The observation was conducted using a small telescope,The object moved in a jerky motion and descended below the horizon,The sighting occurred in Baltimore, Maryland during a period of 20+ winds up to 65 knots.
witness description: The observation was made from a backyard using a small telescope.
